main event: An unidentified flying object with indefinite shape and multiple colors was observed in Baltimore, Maryland, on September 7, 1955.
interesting points: The object emitted lights in red, blue, white, and green colors shooting out at 5-second intervals,The observation lasted approximately 57 seconds,Local astronomers were unable to provide insights on the sighting as they were on summer leave, The object was sighted around the same time Miss Jean Laudlow reported two bright lights flying to the north, Investigation suggested the possibility of the object being an aircraft, balloon, or astronomical phenomenon.
sighted object: indefinite shaped object emitting multi-colored lights
witness description: Military personnel and local observers noted the sighting.
